commentPostTextItems.html: Yesterday, Greg Chappell had said that West Indies have forgotten how to win but today, they have shown that the memory is back!  First, they rallied through a defiant 98 from Sarwan to reach a fighting total and then, prowled the field like hungry tigers, inspiring their bowlers to turn in a disciplined performance to gain a series levelling victory. Wild celebrations are on now. Bravo did a victory run, and the rest of the jubilant West Indians caught up with him near the ropes and they all huddled for a victory jig. Ah! that sweet music of victory! All this while, Yuvraj Singh was hanging almost motionless at the crease, down on his knees, resting on that bat which nearly took India home but failed at the death. Meanwhile Brian Lara was celebrating with his boys. Earlier, he had shuffled his bowlers, threw himself on the field, inspiring his boys to follow his act. Lara has encashed everything that his bat can offer: runs, records, name and fame but captaincy glory has continued to elude him. Destiny has thrown him one last chance, history is calling and Lara, by accepting the top job, has made it clear that he has not gone deaf. It's going to be one long tough climb up the mountain but they have made a start here. Its really too early, to pass any verdict on his latest stint with the captaincy though. But for here and now, it's celebration time for West Indians. And, oh! by the way, the man of the match is ... ... Ramnaresh Sarwan.

commentTextItems.html: OMG! a crashing drive through covers for four! short of length delivery on the stumps, Yuvraj moves away from the stumps, towards the leg side and swats it over cover point for a vital four. 2 runs to win! can yuvraj maintain his cool and can Bravo do it for West Indies?
lucky four! Yuvraj makes room outside the leg stump and tries to hoick it across the line, gets a top edge and it flies just to left of baugh who tries his best to get a hand but .... Game on!

Fires in a yorker but it drifts on the legs, Munaf tries to dig it out, misses and gets a inside edge to the keeper and they scramble through for the vital run that brings yuvraj back onto the strike. 10 off 5 balls! What will Yuvraj Singh do?!

notes: West Indies innings

Over 8.1: Irfan Pathan bowls a delivery to Ramnaresh Sarwan without Billy Doctrove, the Umpire at Square-leg in position. Sarwan pushes one to the on side and they go through for a quick run and Raina, from short midwicket, comes in and throws the stumps down. It is only when the Indian fielders appeal for a run-out that they realise the Umpire was not in position. Umpire Doctrove was at the squareleg fence attending to some sideboards which were causing sighting-problems for the batsmen. The two umpires, Asad Rauf and Billy Doctrove, after consultations, decided to call and signal 'Dead Ball', returned both batsmen to their respective ends, and had that ball bowled again.
